---

AFFECTED AREAS
- theme tokens / color system → risk of inconsistent inheritance
- finance dashboard surfaces → risk of readability regressions
- buttons / nav active states → risk of overusing accent purple
- typography hierarchy → risk of breaking spacing or truncation
- card styling → risk of contrast becoming too low in dark mode

---

RISK AREAS
- dark theme contrast → inaccessible text if secondary text gets too dim
- purple accent usage → can become cheap if over-applied
- progression visuals → can feel gamified if too obvious
- logo treatment → can become generic if too literal
- dashboard restyle → can reduce scannability if aesthetics override hierarchy

---

POTENTIAL BUGS
- theme token replacement → legacy components may retain old colors
- dark surface updates → icons may lose contrast
- CTA styling changes → disabled/hover/focus states may become inconsistent
- typography resizing → overflow or wrapping on smaller mobile widths
- nav/state styling → selected states may become ambiguous

